<br>
&quot;I have heard of this 'Gabrielle' you speak of. However, this is my tribe and no one gets special passage through because they happen to be the daughter of a Queen. Many children of amazons have strayed and gone against the Nation.&quot;<br>
<br>
Her wolfs growled standing and watching this woman, Hope. None of them trusted her at all.<br>
<br>
One stray wolf left the pack and slipped through the village gates where it ran into teh young Elisian girl. He sniffed around her and being a pup, playfully growled at her. He had no cause to worry at all. He smelled Amazon blood in this one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugabbyshope.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GabbysHOPE</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#993300>(2/22/02 1:37:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://images.channeladvisor.com/Sell/SSProfiles/30005913/Images/gabares.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: speaking with Alysia</span><hr size=1> ::she looked to the young pup with a show of amused innocence, very much a show as far as innocence was concerned::<br>
<br>
This young one. This pup. Very much like the scattered tribes of Artemis. I do keep track of them all. And I must say that I am very impressed. No less than a dozen possibly more tribes are within the immediate lands, but how many are so well organized.. so well.. guarded against the inevitable challenges which face us all. Scynthia. Themiscrya. Sarmatia. Certainly they fair well in the winter months. But what of the lesser tribes with few numbers. Fewer warriors to protect them.<br>
<br>
::she allowed the meaning of her words to make themselves known, though she gave a gentle smile::<br>
<br>
No. As you can see I hold no great army before me. And I come here today not to lower myself to direct conflicts with others. ::she generally hired expendable mercenaries for that:: I merely bring warning of those.. shall we say less scrupulous leaders. Ares. Juride. Vstakk. Carrion. Do not be so sure they have left these lands from their ambitions.<br>
<br>
It might do well for the Amazon Nation to find an allie in myself. One who holds the attentions and persuasions to keep these individuals from taking interest. <br>
<br>
And all I ask are but a few precious moments to reflect upon the fallen heroic deeds of the Scynthian Amazons at rest. Perhaps to gain insight upon the mystical runes and charms often carved in wood or stone to guide them in the afterlife to their eternal path. Call it a spiritual quest if you will. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvyiana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vyiana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#993300>(2/22/02 8:31:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: speaking with Alysia</span><hr size=1> ::The younger woman watched the pup closely at its apparent growling, but upon following its gaze with her own eyes as he circled her, she realized no harm would come from him. Daring, she lowered herself to crouch before the wolf and gently outstreached her hand to pet him over his head::<br>
<br>
&quot;I have become lost in these woods.. they are unkown to me.&quot;  She spoke almost to herself as she stood, watching the wolf.  &quot;I ventured too far from my home -  though.. I can sense oddly enough, that I may not be lost at all.&quot;  Once more she gazed about the woods, and made her way straight down the path towards the village, upon seeing it's gates she hid behind a few trees. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=217.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showNextMessage?topicID=217.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.emailToFriend?topicID=217.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.threadControl?topicID=217.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=217.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=217.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub11.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0